<subSubSection id="C32D63FDDE56FFE8FF3FF7DBFEA34A21" pageId="8" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B883076DE56FFE8FF3FF7DBFEDD49C3" blockId="8.[189,335,1412,1438]" box="[189,335,1412,1438]" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">
<heading id="D0C0871ADE56FFE8FF3FF7DBFEDD49C3" bold="true" box="[189,335,1412,1438]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="24" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B943EC64DE56FFE8FF3FF7DBFEDD49C3" bold="true" box="[189,335,1412,1438]" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883076DE56FFE8FF3FF7EDFEA34A21" blockId="8.[189,1400,1458,1660]" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">
Colony unilaminar encrusting. Autozooids subtrigonal to subrectangular, indistinct zooidal boundaries (
<figureCitation id="130C2CF3DE56FFE8FF45F789FEB549AD" box="[199,295,1493,1520]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1045,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-147@9.[189,1398,1045,1889]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Antropora gadhavii Guha &amp; Gopikrishna, 2005 (GIS/B 0461). A. General view of the colony showing autozooids. B–C. Enlargement of the colony showing autozooid and interzooecial avicularia. D. Close-up of the colony showing autozooids with cryptocyst and interzooecial avicularia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6580794" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6580794/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Gymnocyst indistinguishable; cryptocyst narrow, thickly calcified, descending into opesia. Opesia subrectangular to subtriangular in shape, elongate, occupying almost entire frontal area. Distal zooidal margins broad, subrectangular (
<figureCitation id="130C2CF3DE56FFE8FD22F443FCB64A6A" box="[672,804,1564,1591]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1045,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-147@9.[189,1398,1045,1889]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Antropora gadhavii Guha &amp; Gopikrishna, 2005 (GIS/B 0461). A. General view of the colony showing autozooids. B–C. Enlargement of the colony showing autozooid and interzooecial avicularia. D. Close-up of the colony showing autozooids with cryptocyst and interzooecial avicularia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6580794" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6580794/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">Fig. 5B–C</figureCitation>
). Avicularia small, interzooecial, oval with acute rostrum, randomly placed at corners between autozooids, without crossbar (
<figureCitation id="130C2CF3DE56FFE8FBC9F460FB5D4A07" box="[1099,1231,1599,1626]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1045,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-147@9.[189,1398,1045,1889]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Antropora gadhavii Guha &amp; Gopikrishna, 2005 (GIS/B 0461). A. General view of the colony showing autozooids. B–C. Enlargement of the colony showing autozooid and interzooecial avicularia. D. Close-up of the colony showing autozooids with cryptocyst and interzooecial avicularia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6580794" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6580794/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">Fig. 5C–D</figureCitation>
). Ovicells not observed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
